From: "Nalluswami, Kumar" <knalluswam@state.pa.us>

Re: completely unnecessary panic that swept Siliguri, India -- & the
world -- in 1994 ... - Mod.JW>
Just a point of factual correction about the location referred to,
"Siliguri." Siliguri is the site of the deaths from [still
unexplained illness noted in postings to Pro-MED beginning with
20010220.0328, & occurred just about a year ago in 2001. This city is
located in the state of West Bengal, in eastern India.
The plague of 1994 was in western India, in the states of Gujarat &
Maharashtra.
